713852f-a.title: Manhattan: 57th Street (East) - Park Avenue
713852f-a.text:
119 East 57th Street, north side, east of Park Avenue. The facade
of this building was designed by its proprietor, Mr. Todhunter.
About 1925.
Drix Duryea.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

713856f-a.title: Manhattan: 57th Street - Park Avenue
713856f-a.text:
57th Street, north side, west from Park Avenue. The tall build-
ing in the centre is the new Fuller Buildingg, Madison Avenue at
the N.E. corner of 57th Street.
1930.
Ewing Galloway.
NO REPRODUCTTIONS.

722279f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 57th Street
722279f-a.text:
Park Avenue, north from 57th Street, showing faces of buildings on
east side of the avenue.
Note on the N.E. corner of 57th Street the Ritz Tower Apartments
(1926) and on S.E. corner of 5wth Street, the old Arion Society
Building (1887).
About 1931.
Ewing Galloway, Photographer.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

722278f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 57th Street (East)
722278f-a.text:
Park Ave., east side, south from, but not including East 57th Street.
Also shown across the sky line, is the R.C.A. Bl4g., the Waldorf Astoria
Hotel and the Grand Central Bldg.
June 11, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
